<subSubSection pageId="232" pageNumber="233" type="distribution">
<paragraph pageId="232" pageNumber="233">Distribution.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="232" pageNumber="233">
This subspecies, the &quot;Sigmoid Tiger Beetle&quot;, is found along the Pacific Coast from southern California (Nagano 1982: 38) to the Baja California Peninsula (Cazier 1954: 291); it is occasionally found inland, as far as the Salton Sea in Imperial County (see LaRue 1991). The record from 
<normalizedToken originalValue="“Arizona”">&quot;Arizona&quot;</normalizedToken>
(Freitag 1999: 74) needs confirmation.
</paragraph>
